a(n) = (-1)^binomial(n,2) = (-1)^floor(n/2) = 1/2*((n+2) mod 4 - n mod 4). For fixed r = 0,1,2,..., it appears that (-1)^binomial(n,2^r) gives a periodic sequence of period 2^(r+1), the period consisting of a block of 2^r plus ones followed by a block of 2^r minus ones. See A033999 (r = 0), A143621 (r = 2) and A143622 (r = 3). Define E(k) = sum {n = 0..inf} a(n)*n^k/n! for k = 0,1,2,... . Then E(0) = cos(1) + sin(1), E(1) = cos(1) - sin(1) and E(k) is an integral linear combination of E(0) and E(1) (a Dobinski-type relation). Precisely, E(k) = A121867(k) * E(0) - A121868(k) * E(1). See A143623 and A143624 for the decimal expansions of E(0) and E(1) respectively. For a fixed value of r, similar relations hold between the values of the sums E_r(k) := Sum_{n>=0} (-1)^floor(n/r)*n^k/n!, k = 0,1,2,... . For particular cases see A000587 (r = 1) and A143628 (r = 3). - _Peter Bala_, Aug 28 2008
a(n) = (1/2)*((1-i)*i^n + (1+i)*(-i)^n), with i=sqrt(-1). - _Paolo P. Lava_, May 26 2010

A057501.name: Signature-permutation of a Catalan Automorphism: Rotate non-crossing chords (handshake) arrangements; rotate the root position of general trees as encoded by A014486.

[This formula reflects directly the given non-destructive Lisp/Scheme function: A085201 is a 2-ary function corresponding to 'append', A072771 and A072772 correspond to 'car' and 'cdr' (known also as first/rest or head/tail in some dialects), and A057548 corresponds to unary form of function 'list'].
As a composition of related permutations:
A129599(a(n)) = A129599(n) holds for all n.

[This formula reflects the S-expression implementation given first in the Program section: A085201 is a 2-ary function corresponding to 'append', A072771 and A072772 correspond to 'car' and 'cdr' (known also as first/rest or head/tail in some languages), and A057548 corresponds to the unary form of function 'list'].

a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n+1} Sum_{i=1..k} C(i+k-1,k). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Sep 19 2017

A057553.name: Rank of (1,1,...,1) (n 1's) when {0,1,2,...}^n is lexicographically ordered.

A057554.name: Lexicographic ordering of MxM, where M={0,1,2,...}.

A057555.name: Lexicographic ordering of N x N, where N = {1,2,3...}.
formula: Let p(i,j) be the position of (i,j) in the ordering. Then p(i,j) = ((i+j)^2-i-3j+2)/2. Inversely, the pair (i,j) in a given position p is given by i=p-q(q-1)/2 and j=q+1-i, where q=floor((1+sqrt(8k-7))/2).

A057556.name: Lexicographic ordering of M x M x M, where M={0,1,2,...}.

A057557.name: Lexicographic ordering of NxNxN, where N={1,2,3,...}.

A057558.name: Lexicographic ordering of MxMxMxM, where M={0,1,2,...}.

A057559.name: Lexicographic ordering of NxNxNxN, where N={1,2,3,...}.

A057560.name: Weakly distance-regular digraphs on n nodes (excluding distance-regular graphs).

A057561.name: Size of the largest set encompassing no {x, 2x, 3x} contained in D(n) = the first n 3-smooth numbers {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9, 12, 16, 18, 24, 27, ...} (A003586).

A057562.name: Number of partitions of n into parts all relatively prime to n.
formula: Coefficient of x^n in expansion of 1/Product_{d : gcd(d, n)=1} (1-x^d). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Dec 23 2004

A057563.name: Numbers k such that the k initial decimal digits of e - 2 form a prime number.

A057564.name: Natural numbers n for which the following three properties hold: (i) Phi[Sigma[n]]=2*phi(n), (ii) Sigma[n-2]=2*Sigma[Phi[n-2]], (iii) Sigma[n+2]=2*Sigma[Phi[n+2]].

A057565.name: Number of regions of linearity for Lusztig's piecewise-linear function in type A_n.

A057566.name: Number of collinear triples in a 3 X n rectangular grid.
formula: Conjecture: a(n) = 5*floor((2n^3 - 3n^2 - n)/24) + floor((2(n-1)^3 - 3(n-1)^2 - (n-1))/24) + n, which fits all of the listed terms.
a(n) = a(n-1) + b(n), with a(0)=-2, b(0)=8 and being b(n) = b(n-1) - 7 + Sum_{k=0..n} (5*(k mod 2) + ((k+1) mod 2)). - _Paolo P. Lava_, Aug 24 2007

A057567.name: Number of partitions of n where the product of parts divides n.
formula: Sum_{ d divides n } A001055(d). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Nov 19 2000
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s) * Product_{k>=2} 1/(1 - 1/k^s). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Nov 03 2020

A057568.name: Number of partitions of n where n divides the product of the parts.

A057569.name: Numbers of the form k*(5*k+1)/2 or k*(5*k-1)/2.
formula: |A113428(n)| is the characteristic function of the numbers a(n).
a(n) = a(1 - n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 13 2012

A057570.name: Numbers of the form n*(7n+-1)/2.
formula: a(n)-a(n-2) = A047341(n-1) for n>2. - _Bruno Berselli_, Jan 25 2011

A057572.name: Number of unlabeled Hugenholz diagrams with n nodes.

A057573.name: Number of primes in A051351 which have index <= 10^n.

A057574.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with n binary coordinates and 1 ternary coordinate with Hamming distance 3.

A057575.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with n binary coordinates and 2 ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057576.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with n binary coordinates and 3 ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057577.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with n binary coordinates and 4 ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057578.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in ternary code of length n with Hamming distance 3.

A057579.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 1 binary coordinate and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057580.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 2 binary coordinates and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057581.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 3 binary coordinates and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057582.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 4 binary coordinates and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057583.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 5 binary coordinates and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057584.name: Maximal numbers of codewords in mixed code with 6 binary coordinates and n ternary coordinates with Hamming distance 3.

A057588.name: Kummer numbers: -1 + product of first n consecutive primes.

A057589.name: Numbers n which are both lucky (A000959) and Fibonacci (A000045).

A057591.name: Maximal size of binary code of length n that corrects 2 deletions.

A057593.name: Triangle T(n, k) giving period length of the periodic sequence k^i (i >= imin) mod n (n >= 2, 1 <= k <= n-1).

A057594.name: Triangle T(n,k) giving floor( (2*p mod n-1)/2), where p = period of sequence k^i (i=0,1,2,...) mod n (n >= 2, 2<=k<=n).

A057595.name: Triangle T(n,k) giving 2*p mod n-1, where p = period of sequence k^i (i=0,1,2,...) mod n (n >= 2, 2<=k<=n).

A057597.name: a(n) = -a(n-1) - a(n-2) + a(n-3), a(0)=0, a(1)=0, a(2)=1.
formula: G.f.: Q(0)*x^2/2, where Q(k) = 1 + 1/(1 - x*(4*k+1 + x - x^2)/( x*(4*k+3 + x - x^2) - 1/Q(k+1) )); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Sep 09 2013
G.f. -x*T(1/x), where T is the g.f. of A000073. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 26 2018

A057599.name: a(n) = (n^2)!/(n!)^(n+1); number of ways of dividing n^2 labeled items into n unlabeled boxes of n items each.

A057600.name: a(n) is smallest number m such that (m = product of n distinct primes) and all divisors of m are lucky numbers.

A057601.name: a(0) = a(1) = 1; a(n+1) is the number of partitions of n into parts a(k), 0 <= k <= n, each k occurring at most once.

A057602.name: a(1)=2, a(n+1) is the smallest integer > a(n) such that the smallest prime factor of a(n+1) is the largest prime factor of a(n).
formula: Even numbered terms are squares of successive primes. Odd numbered terms are the product of two successive primes and are the square root of the product of the previous term and the next term - _Jud McCranie_, Oct 07 2000

A057603.name: Second term of continued fraction for log(n).

A057605.name: Nonnegative n such that 4*n^2 + 163 is prime.

A057606.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of binary n-tuples u having exactly k grandchildren, where a grandchild is a vector obtained by deleting any two coordinates of u (n >= 3, 1<=k<=2^(n-2)).

A057607.name: Triangle T(n,k) = number of binary n-tuples u having exactly k grandchildren, where a grandchild is a vector obtained by deleting any two coordinates of u (n >= 2, 0<=k<=2^(n-2)).

A057608.name: Maximal size of binary code of length n that corrects one transposition (end-around transposition not included).

A057609.name: Powers of a prime lucky number (A031157) but excluding lucky numbers (A000959).

A057610.name: Smallest lucky number containing leading sequence of n descending numbers.

A057611.name: Let m = 3, 5, 7, ..., k = 0, 1, 2, 3, ..., z = (m+1)/2, 0 < j <= m. Let n_j be a prime number. Sequence gives T(m,k) = Table[m,k] = number of solutions to Sum_{d=1,2, ..., (z+k)}(n_j)_d = Sum_{d=1,2, ..., (z-k-1)}(n_j)_d = primorial number (A002110).
formula: A022894(m) = Sum_{k=0, 1, 2, ..} [Number of solutions to Sum_{d=1, 2, ..., (z+k)}(n_j)_d = Sum_{ d=1, 2, ..., (z-k-1)}(n_j)_d]

A057612.name: Numbers that are both Mersenne numbers (A001348) and lucky numbers (A000959).

A057613.name: Numbers that are both lucky numbers (A000959) and of form 2^k-1.

A057614.name: a(n+1) = a(n)/2 if 2|a(n), a(n)/3 if 3|a(n), a(n)/5 if 5|a(n), a(n)/7 if 7|a(n), otherwise 11*a(n)+1.

A057615.name: ATS: Add Then Sort (i.e., double previous term and then sort digits).

A057616.name: Lucky numbers that are the product of the first m lucky numbers for some m.

A057617.name: Order of subgroup bP_{m+1} of group Theta_m of h-cobordism classes of smooth homotopy m-spheres defined by those homotopy m-spheres which bound parallelizable (m+1)-manifolds, where m = 2n+1.

A057618.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 1 modulo 5.

A057619.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 3 modulo 4.

A057620.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n consecutive primes congruent to 1 modulo 6.

A057621.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 2 modulo 3.
formula: a(n) = A000040(A247967(n)) for all n > 1. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 03 2016

A057622.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n consecutive primes congruent to 5 modulo 6.

A057623.name: a(n) = n! * (sum of reciprocals of all parts in unrestricted partitions of n).
formula: n! *sum_{k=1 to n} [sigma(k) p(n-k) /k], where sigma(n) = sum of positive divisors of n and p(n) = number of unrestricted partitions of n.
a(n) = P(n,1), where P(n,m) = P(n,m+1)+S(n-m,m)*n!/m+n!/(n-m)!*P(n-m,m)), P(n,n)=(n-1)!, P(n,m)=0 for m>n, S(n,m) is triangle of A026807. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Sep 10 2014

A057624.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 1 modulo 4.

A057625.name: a(n) = n! * sum 1/k! where the sum is over all positive integers k that divide n.
formula: Equals the logarithmic derivative of A209903. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Jul 26 2012

A057626.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 2 modulo 5.

A057627.name: Number of nonsquarefree numbers not exceeding n.
formula: G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} (1 - mu(k)^2)*x^k/(1 - x). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 17 2017

A057628.name: Primes such that replacing each digit d with d copies of the digit d produces a prime. Zeros are not allowed.

A057629.name: Number of alternating sign 2n X 2n matrices invariant under flips in both diagonals.

A057630.name: Primes such that replacing each digit d with d copies of the digit d produces a prime. Zeros are allowed.

A057631.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 3 modulo 5.

A057632.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 3 modulo 8.

A057633.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 5 modulo 8.

A057634.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 7 modulo 8.

A057635.name: a(n) is the largest m such that phi(m) = n, where phi is Euler's totient function = A000010.
formula: a(2n+1) = 0 for n > 0 and when a(2n) = 0, the nontotients (A005277)/2.

A057636.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 4 modulo 5. The first prime in a sequence of length n all ending with the digit 9.

A057637.name: a(n) is the largest number such that sigma(a(n)) = n, where sigma is the sum of divisors function (A000203).

A057638.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 1 modulo 8.

A057639.name: First differences of zero-sites (A028442) of Mertens's function A002321.

A057641.name: a(n) = floor(H(n) + exp(H(n))*log(H(n))) - sigma(n), where H(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} 1/k and sigma(n) (A000203) is the sum of the divisors of n.

A057642.name: (Product k^k) * (Sum 1/k^k) where both the sum and product are over those positive integers k that divide n.

A057643.name: Least common multiple of all (k+1)'s, where the k's are the positive divisors of n.

A057644.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 1 modulo 9.

A057645.name: Initial prime in first sequence of n primes congruent to 2 modulo 9.

A057646.name: a(n) is the number of trinomials x^n + x^k + 1 that are irreducible over GF(2) for some k with n > k > 0.

A057647.name: Number of walks of length n on the upper-right part of the honeycomb lattice.

A057648.name: Number of excursions of length n on the upper-right part of the honeycomb lattice.

A057649.name: Nearest integer to ratio of volume of n-dimensional cube of side 2 to volume of n-dimensional ball of radius 1.

A057650.name: Second step in Goodstein sequences, i.e., g(4) if g(2)=n: (first step) write g(2)=n in hereditary representation base 2, bump to base 3, then subtract 1 to produce g(3)=A056004(n), then (second step) write g(3) in hereditary representation base 3, bump to base 4, then subtract 1 to produce g(4).

A057652.name: Numbers n such that n-2^k is a lucky number for all k such that 1 < 2^k < n.

A057653.name: Odd numbers of form x^2 + y^2.
formula: n = odd square * {product of distinct primes == 1 (mod 4)}.

A057654.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n)^2 - phi(n)^2 is a perfect square.

A057655.name: The circle problem: number of points (x,y) in square lattice with x^2 + y^2 <= n.
formula: a(n) - Pi*n = O(sqrt(n)) (Gauss). a(n) - Pi*n = O(n^c), c = 23/73 + epsilon ~ 0.3151 (Huxley). If a(n) - Pi*n = O(n^c) then c > 1/4 (Landau, Hardy). It is conjectured that a(n) - Pi*n = O(n^(1/4 + epsilon)) for all epsilon > 0.

a(n) = 1 + sum((floor(1/(k+1)) + 4 * floor(cos(Pi * sqrt(k))^2) - 4 * floor(cos(Pi * sqrt(k/2))^2) + 8 * sum((floor(cos(Pi * sqrt(i))^2) * floor(cos(Pi * sqrt(k-i))^2)), i = 1..floor(k/2))), k = 1..n). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 10 2013
G.f.: theta_3(0,x)^2/(1-x) where theta_3 is a Jacobi theta function. - _Robert Israel_, Sep 29 2014

A057656.name: Number of points (x,y) in square lattice with (x-1/2)^2+y^2 <= n.

A057657.name: Maximal size of binary code of length n that corrects one transposition (end-around transposition included).

A057659.name: Prime numbers whose square is composed of just two different decimal digits.

A057660.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} n/gcd(n,k).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{d|n} d*A000010(d) = Sum_{d|n} d*A054522(n,d), sum of d times phi(d) for all divisors d of n, where phi is Euler's phi function.
a(n) = Sum_{d|n} A000010(d^2). - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, Jul 12 2010
a(n) <= (n-1)*n + 1, with equality if and only if n is noncomposite. - _Daniel Forgues_, Apr 30 2013

G.f.: Sum_{n >= 1} n*phi(n)*x^n/(1 - x^n) = x + 3*x^2 + 7*x^3 + 11*x^4 + .... Dirichlet g.f.: sum {n >= 1} a(n)/n^s = zeta(s)*zeta(s-2)/zeta(s-1) for Re s > 3.  Cf. A078747 and A176797. - _Peter Bala_, Dec 30 2013
a(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} numerator(n/i). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Feb 26 2017
L.g.f.: -log(Product_{k>=1} (1 - x^k)^phi(k)) = Sum_{n>=1} a(n)*x^n/n. - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, May 21 2018

A057661.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} lcm(n,k)/n.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{d|n} psi(d), where psi(m) = is the sum of totatives of m (A023896). - _Jaroslav Krizek_, Dec 28 2016
a(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} denominator(n/i). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Feb 26 2017
G.f.: x/(2*(1 - x)) + (1/2)*Sum_{k>=1} k*phi(k)*x^k/(1 - x^k), where phi() is the Euler totient function (A000010). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Aug 31 2017
If p is prime, then a(p) = T(p-1) + 1 = p(p-1)/2 + 1, where T(n) = n(n+1)/2 is the n-th triangular number (A000217). - _David Terr_, Feb 10 2019
Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ zeta(3) * n^3 / Pi^2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 29 2021

A057662.name: Smallest prime q(n) such that q(n)+2^p(n) is a prime, where p(n) is the n-th prime.

A057663.name: Primes p such that p + 2^p is also a prime.

A057664.name: Primes of the form p + 2^p where p is prime.

A057665.name: Numbers n such that prime(n)+2^prime(n) is prime.

A057667.name: Primes q of form q = 10p + 3, where p is an odd prime.

A057668.name: Number of minimal 7-covers of a labeled n-set.

A057669.name: Triangle T(n,k) of number of minimal 3-covers of an unlabeled n+3-set that cover k points of that set uniquely (k=3,..,n+3).
formula: T(n, k) = b(n, k)-b(n-1, k); b(n, k) = coefficient of x^k in x^3/6*(Z(S_n; 5+3*x, 5+3*x^2, ...)+3*Z(S_n; 3+x, 5+3*x^2, 3+x^3, 5+3*x^4, ...)+2*Z(S_n; 2, 2, 5+3*x^3, 2, 2, 5+3*x^6, ...)), where Z(S_n; x_1, x_2, ..., x_n) is cycle index of symmetric group S_n of degree n.

A057670.name: a(n) = Sum_{k|n} lcm(k, n/k).
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ 3*Zeta(3)*n^2 / (2*Pi^2) * (2*log(n) - 24*Zeta'(2)/Pi^2 - 1 + 4*gamma + 4*Zeta'(3)/Zeta(3)), where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 01 2019

A057671.name: a(n) equals floor(Vc(n) - Vs(n)), where Vc(n) is the volume of the cube with side length n and Vs(n) is the volume of the sphere of diameter n.

A057672.name: a(n) equals floor(As(n) - Ac(n)), where As(n) is the area of the square with side length n and Ac(n) is the area of the circle of diameter n.

A057673.name: Smallest prime p such that |2^n - p| is a prime.

A057674.name: Primes -p+2^n with smallest p prime, arising in A057674.

A057676.name: Smallest prime q(n) such that -q(n)+2^p(n) is a prime, where p(n) = n-th prime.

A057677.name: a(n) is the numerator of b(n) where b(n)=1/b(n-1)+1/b(n-2) with b(1)=1 and b(2)=2.
formula: a(n) satisfies the cubic recurrence : a(1)=1, a(2)=2, a(3)=3, a(4)=7, a(5)=32 and for n>=6 a(n)=a(n-2)^2*a(n-3)+a(n-1)*a(n-3)*a(n-4)
lim_{n->infty} b(n)=sqrt(2) with geometric convergence since abs(b(n)-sqrt(2))<2*2^(-n/2)

A057678.name: Primes of the form 2^p - p where p is prime.

A057679.name: Self-locating strings within Pi: numbers n such that the string n is at position n in the decimal digits of Pi, where 3 is the first digit.

A057680.name: Self-locating strings within Pi: numbers n such that the string n is at position n in the decimal digits of Pi, where 1 is the first digit.

A057681.name: a(n) = Sum_{j=0..floor(n/3)} (-1)^j*binomial(n,3*j).
formula: Start with x(0)=1,y(0)=0,z(0)=0 and set x(n+1)=x(n)-z(n), y(n+1)=y(n)-x(n),z(n+1)=z(n)-y(n). Then a(n)=x(n). But this recurrence falls into a repetitive cycle of length 6 and multiplicative factor -27, so that a(n) = -27*a(n-6) for any n>6. - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jun 10 2012
a(n+m) = a(n)*a(m)-A057682(n)*A*057083(m)-A*057083(n)*A057682(m), where A*057083 is A057083 prefixed by two 0's. - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Jun 25 2017

A057682.name: a(n) = Sum_{j=0..floor(n/3)} (-1)^j*binomial(n,3*j+1).
formula: Starting at 1, the binomial transform of A000484. - _Paul Barry_, Jul 21 2003
It appears that abs(a(n)) = floor(abs(A000748(n))/3). - _John W. Layman_, Sep 05 2003

Let A(n) be the n X n matrix with -1's along the main diagonal, 1's everywhere above the main diagonal, and 1's along the subdiagonal. Then a(n) equals (-1)^(n-1) times the sum of the coefficients of the characteristic polynomial of A(n-1), for all n>1 (see Mathematica code below). - _John M. Campbell_, Mar 16 2012

Start with x(0)=1, y(0)=0, z(0)=0 and set x(n+1)=x(n)-z(n), y(n+1)=y(n)-x(n), z(n+1)=z(n)-y(n). Then a(n)=-y(n). But this recurrence falls into a repetitive cycle of length 6 and multiplicative factor -27, so that a(n) = -27*a(n-6) for any n>6. - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jun 10 2012
G.f.: 3*x - 1/3 + 3*x/(G(0) - 1) where G(k)= 1 + 3*(2*k+3)*x/(2*k+1 - 3*x*(k+2)*(2*k+1)/(3*x*(k+2) + (k+1)/G(k+1)));(continued fraction, 3rd kind, 3-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Nov 23 2012
G.f.: Q(0,u) -1, where u=x/(1-x), Q(k,u) = 1 - u^2 + (k+2)*u - u*(k+1 - u)/Q(k+1); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Oct 07 2013

A057683.name: Numbers k such that k^2+k+1, k^3+k+1 and k^4+k+1 are all prime.

A057688.name: Trajectory of 5 under the '5x+1' map.
formula: a(0) = 5, a(n) = a(n - 1)/2 if a(n - 1) is even, a(n) = a(n - 1)/3 if a(n - 1) is odd and divisible by 3, a(n) = 5a(n - 1) otherwise.

A057689.name: Maximal term in trajectory of P under the 'Px+1' map, where P = n-th prime, or -1 if no such term exists.

A057690.name: Length of cycle in trajectory of P under the 'Px+1' map, where P = n-th prime, or -1 if trajectory does not cycle.
formula: a(n) = A023514(n)+1 if the cycle contains the number 1. - _Jon Maiga_, Jan 12 2021

A057691.name: Number of terms before entering cycle in trajectory of P under the 'Px+1' map, where P = n-th prime, or -1 if trajectory does not cycle.

A057692.name: Smallest prime which produces exactly n+1 different primes after n applications of the A048376 transform.

A057693.name: Number of permutations on n letters that have only cycles of length 3 or less.
formula: E.g.f.: exp( x + (x^2)/2 + (x^3)/3 ). Replacing 3 by "length k or less" in the definition of the sequence the E.g.f. is exp( x + (x^2)/2 + ... + (x^k)/k ). - Sharon Sela (sharonsela(AT)hotmail.com), May 16 2002

a(n) = a(n-1)+(n-1)*a(n-2)+(n-1)(n-2)*a(n-3). Generally, for n-permutations that have only cycles of length k or less the recurrence is: a(n)=Sum_i=0...k-1;P(n-1,i)*a(n-i-1) where P(x,i) is the falling factorial. - _Geoffrey Critzer_, May 23 2009

A057694.name: Chance of holding n-th best poker hand or better is approximately 1/a(n).

A057695.name: Number of 5-card poker hands with deuces wild of 5-of-a-kind, royal flush, straight flush, 4-of-a-kind, full house, flush, straight, 3-of-a-kind, two pairs, one pair, no pair.

A057696.name: Number of letters in n in Brazilian Portuguese (not counting spaces).
formula: Zero, um, dois, tres, quatro, cinco, seis, sete, oito, nove, dez, onze, doze, treze, quatorze, quinze, dezesseis, dezessete, dezoito, dezenove, vinte, vinte e um, vinte e dois, vinte e tres, vinte e quatro, vinte e cinco, vinte e seis, vinte e sete, vinte e oito, vinte e nove, trinta, ...

A057697.name: Number of characters in n (including spaces) in Brazilian Portuguese.

A057698.name: Prime lucky numbers k (from A031157) such that nextprime(k)=nextlucky(k).

A057699.name: Primes whose reversal is a cube.

A057700.name: The next new gap between successive lucky numbers.

A057701.name: Twin lucky numbers: (n,m) are lucky numbers with |n-m|=2.

A057702.name: Even numbers not the sum of a pair of twin lucky numbers.

A057704.name: Primorial - 1 prime indices: integers n such that the n-th primorial minus 1 is prime.

A057705.name: Primorial primes: primes p such that p+1 is a primorial number (A002110).

A057706.name: Smaller of twin primes whose average is a primorial number.

A057707.name: Number of poly-octagon squares: a(n) = number of 'polyominoes' that can be formed by n octagons and n squares (of perimeter 8m and 4m respectively) not counting rotations or reflections such that the resulting objects will fit on the plane that is uniformly tiled by the same size octagons and squares.

A057708.name: Numbers n such that 2^n reversed is prime.

A057709.name: Numbers k such that there is a unique m for which the sum of the aliquot parts of m (A001065) is k.

A057710.name: Positive integers k with exactly 2 aliquot sequence predecessors. In other words, there are exactly two solutions x for which s(x) = n. The function s(x) here is the sum of all proper divisors of x (A001065).

A057711.name: a(0)=0, a(1)=1, a(n) = n*2^(n-2) for n >= 2.
formula: The sequence 1, 1, 6, 16, ... is the binomial transform of A016813 with interpolated zeros. - _Paul Barry_, Jul 25 2003
For n > 1, a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (k-n/2)^2 C(n, k). (n+1)*a(n) = A001788(n). - Mario Catalani (mario.catalani(AT)unito.it), Nov 26 2003

A057712.name: Number of "polyhes" of order n: a polyhe of order n is obtained by taking a polyhex made of n hexagons (A000228); cutting each of the n hexagons along a diameter and throwing away half that hexagon, in such a way that the remaining figure (made of n half-hexagons) is connected.

A057713.name: Smallest prime divisor of Kummer numbers ( = primorials - 1), or 1 if no such prime exists.

A057714.name: If (p_k)^(c_k) is highest power of p_k dividing n (where p_k is a prime dividing n and p_k > p_j for all k > j), then (p_k)^(c_k) > (p_j)^(c_j) for all k > j.

A057715.name: If (p_k)^(c_k) is highest power of p_k dividing n (where p_k is a prime dividing n and p_k > p_j for all k > j), then (p_k)^(c_k) < (p_j)^(c_j) for all k > j.

A057716.name: The non-powers of 2.
formula: a(n) = n + [log_2(n + [log_2(n)])] gives this sequence with the exception of a(1) = 1. - _David W. Wilson_, Mar 29 2005
Find k such that 2^k - (k + 1) <= n < 2^(k+1) - (k + 2), then a(n) = n + k + 1.
Numbers n = 2a(k) - 1, k > 0 are such that Sum_{k=0..n} B_k*M(n-k)*binomial(n, k) = 0 where B_k is the k-th Bernoulli number and M_k the k-th Motzkin number. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Oct 19 2005

A057717.name: The non-powers of 10.
formula: Find k such that 10^k - (k + 1) <= n < 10^(k+1) - (k + 2), then a(n) = n + k + 1.

A057718.name: A036917/8 (omitting leading term of A036917).
formula: G.f.: 7/8 + (1/2)*(K(16x)/pi)^2, where K(x) is the elliptic integral of the first kind (as defined in Mathematica). - _Emanuele Munarini_, Mar 12 2011
a(n) = (1/8)*sum(binomial(2k,k)^2*binomial(2n-2k,n-k)^2, k=0..n) for n >= 1. - _Emanuele Munarini_, Mar 12 2011

A057719.name: Prime factors of numbers in A006521 (numbers n such that n divides 2^n+1).

A057720.name: Decimal expansion of muon-to-electron mass ratio.

A057721.name: a(n) = n^4 + 3*n^2 + 1.
formula: a(n) = denominator of Integral_{x=0..infinity} sin(n*x)/exp((n^2+1)*x). - _Francesco Daddi_, Jul 07 2013

A057723.name: Sum of positive divisors of n that are divisible by every prime that divides n.
formula: If n = Product p_i^e_i then a(n) = Product (p_i + p_i^2 + ... + p_i^e_i).
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s) * zeta(s-1) * Product(p prime, 1 - p^(-s) + p^(1-2*s)). - _Robert Israel_, May 13 2015
a(n) = Sum_{d|n, rad(d)=rad(n)} d. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jun 02 2020
a(n) = Sum_{d|n, gcd(d, n/d) = 1} (-1)^omega(n/d) * sigma(d). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 15 2021

A057724.name: Number of "polyares" of order n (turning over allowed).

A057725.name: Number of "polyares" of order n (turning over not allowed).

A057728.name: A triangular table of decreasing powers of two (with first column all ones).
formula: G.f.: (x - x^2)/((1 - 2*x)*(1 - y*x)). - _Geoffrey Critzer_, Jan 28 2014 [This produces the triangle shown by _Mats Granvik_ in example section. - _Franck Maminirina Ramaharo_, Jan 09 2019]

A057729.name: Number of triangular polyominoes (or polyiamonds) [A000577] with perimeter n.

A057731.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of elements of order k in symmetric group S_n, for n >= 1, 1 <= k <= g(n), where g(n) = A000793(n) is Landau's function..
formula: Sum_{k=1..A000793(n)} k*T(n,k) = A060014(n); A000793 = Landau's function.

A057732.name: Numbers n such that 2^n + 3 is prime.
formula: Here is an LLT-like algorithm, using a cycle of the digraph x^2-2 modulo N, that finds terms of this sequence generating a PRP (PRobable Prime) of A057733 numbers: N=2^n+3; S0=(N-5)/2; s(0)=S0; s(i+1)=s(i)^2-2 modulo N; if s(n-1) == S0 then N is prime. - _Tony Reix_, Aug 27 2015

A057736.name: Primes p such that 2^p + 3 is prime.

A057737.name: Primes of the form 2^p + 3, where p is prime.

A057738.name: Primes p such that 3^p + 2 is prime.

A057739.name: Primes of the form 3^p + 2, where p is prime.

A057740.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of elements of alternating group A_n having order k, for n >= 1, 1<=k<=A051593(n).

A057741.name: Table T(n,k) giving number of elements of order k in dihedral group D_{2n} of order 2n, n >= 1, 1<=k<=g(n), where g(n) = 2 if n=1 else g(n) = n.
formula: If k<>2 and k does not divide n, this number is 0; if k<>2 and k divides n, this number is phi(k), where phi is the Euler totient function; if k=2, this number is n for odd n and n+1 for even n.

A057742.name: Maximal order of element of alternating group A_{2n}.

A057743.name: Maximal order of element of alternating group A_{2n+1}.

A057746.name: Even numbers not the sum of a pair of twin even-lucky-numbers (from A045955, A045956).

A057747.name: Number of decompositions of 2n-1 into sum of a lucky number and an even-lucky-number (from A045954).

A057748.name: Number of decompositions of 2n-1 into sum of a twin lucky number and a twin even-lucky-number (from A045955, A045956).

A057749.name: Prime degrees of absolutely reducible trinomials: primes p such that x^p + x^k + 1 is reducible over GF(2) for all k, p>k>0.

A057750.name: Number of non-factorable subsets of size >= 2 of a 1 X n uniform grid.

A057751.name: Irreducible trinomials of prime degree for some k: x^p + x^k + 1 is irreducible over GF(2) for at least one k, p>k>0.

A057752.name: Difference between nearest integer to Li(10^n) and pi(10^n), where Li(x) = integral of log(x) and  pi(10^n) = number of primes <= 10^n (A006880).

A057753.name: Total area of all polyominoes with perimeter 2n.

A057754.name: Integer nearest to Li(10^n), where Li(x) = integral(0..x, dt/log(t)).
formula: a(n) = round( Li( 10^n )) = round( Ei( log( 10^n ))).

A057755.name: Number of digits in n-th Fermat number (A000215).
formula: a(n) = floor(log_10(F_n)+1) (F_n is the n-th Fermat number). - _Ivan Panchenko_, Sep 06 2009

A057756.name: Least nonnegative square root of -1 mod n for n in A008784.

A057757.name: Least nonnegative square root of 2 mod n for n in A057126.

A057759.name: Least nonnegative square root of 3 mod n for n in A057125.

A057760.name: Numbers n such that 2 is a cube mod n.

A057761.name: Least nonnegative cube root of 2 mod n for n in A057760.

A057762.name: Numbers n such that 5 is a square mod n.

A057763.name: Least nonnegative square root of 5 mod n for n in A057762.

A057764.name: Triangle T(n,k) = number of nonzero elements of multiplicative order k in Galois field GF(2^n) (n >= 1, 1 <= k <= 2^n-1).
formula: T(n,k) = A000010(k) if k is a divisor of 2^n-1, otherwise 0.

A057765.name: Number of factorable subsets of a 1 X n uniform grid.

A057766.name: Total area of all n-celled polyominoes.

A057767.name: Number of twin prime pairs between P(n)^2 and P(n+1)^2 where P(n) is the n-th prime.

A057768.name: From Goldbach problem: number of decompositions of 2n-1 into sum of a prime lucky number(from A031157) and a twin even-lucky-number(from A045955, A045956).

A057770.name: The primes in A045574.
formula: Primes containing the digits 0, 1, 6, 8 or 9 only.

A057771.name: Number of loops (quasigroups with an identity element) of order n.

A057773.name: Sum_{i=1..n} nu_2 ( prime(i) - 1), where prime(i) is the i-th prime and nu_2(m) = exponent of highest power of 2 dividing m.

A057774.name: Values of k corresponding to A073571.

A057775.name: a(n) is the least prime p such that p-1 is divisible by 2^n and not by 2^(n+1).

A057776.name: a(n)-th prime is smallest such that p(a[n])-1 is divisible by 2^(n-1) and quotient is odd.

A057777.name: a(n) is the smallest number such that a(n)+1 is a prime and the largest power of 2 which divides it is 2^n.

A057778.name: a(n) is the least odd k such that k*2^n + 1 is prime.
formula: a(n) = Min{k: 1+2^n*k is prime and k is odd}.
a(n) << 19^n by Xylouris's improvement to Linnik's theorem. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Dec 10 2013

A057779.name: Hexagonal polyominoes (or polyhexes, A000228) with perimeter 2n.

A057780.name: Multiples of 3 that are one less than a perfect square.

A057781.name: a(n) = n^4+4 = (n^2-2*n+2)*(n^2+2*n+2) = ((n-1)^2+1)*((n+1)^2+1).
formula: Sum_{k=0..n} A033999(k)*A016755(k)/a(k) = A033999(n)*(n+1)/A053755(n+1), see Knuth reference. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 11 2010

A057782.name: Building block is trapezoid formed from 3 equilateral triangles; sequence gives number of pieces (polytraps) that can be formed from n such trapezoids.

A057783.name: Building block is 2 hexagons side-by-side; sequence gives number of pieces (polydohexes) that can be formed from n such pairs of hexagons.

A057784.name: Number of polypons with n cells.

A057785.name: Blunt polypons (no 30-degree angles) with n cells.

A057786.name: Number of polykites with n cells.

A057787.name: Number of polyarcs with n cells.

A057788.name: Expansion of (1+x)/(1-x)^12.
formula: a(n) = C(n+10,10) + 2*C(n+10,11). - Borislav St. Borisov (b.st.borisov(AT)abv.bg), Mar 05 2009

A057789.name: a(n) = Sum_{k = 1..n, gcd(k,n)=1} k*(n-k).
formula: If n is prime, a(n) = A000292(n-1).
If n/2 is an odd prime, a(n) =  A000292(n-2)/2.
If n/3 is a prime other than 3, a(n) = A000292(n-3)*2*n/(3*(n-2)). (End)

A057790.name: Table read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) = number of restricted knight's walks from (n,k) (n >= 0, k >= 0).

A057791.name: Sum[k^(n-k)], where sum is over positive integers, k, where k <= n and gcd(k,n) = 1.

A057792.name: Sum[k^k], where sum is over positive integers, k, where k <= n and gcd(k,n) = 1.

A057793.name: Integer nearest Riemann(10^n), where Riemann(x) = Sum of ( mu(k)/k * Integral Log( x^(1/k) ) for k = 1 to infinity.

A057794.name: (Integer nearest R(10^n)) - pi(10^n), where pi(x) is the number of primes <= x, R(x) = Sum_{ k>=1 } (mu(k)/k * li(x^(1/k))) and li(x) is the Cauchy principal value of the integral from 0 to x of dt/log(t).

A057795.name: Sum k!, where sum is over positive integers k <= n with gcd(k,n) = 1.

A057796.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in deuces-wild poker.

A057797.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, full house, flush, 4 of a kind, straight, 2 pair, 3 of a kind, a pair in deuces-wild poker.

A057798.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 2 jokers.

A057799.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 1 joker.

A057800.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 2 pair, 3 of a kind, a pair in wild-card poker with 2 jokers.

A057801.name: Number of ways of getting 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 2 pair, 3 of a kind, a pair in wild-card poker with 2 jokers.

A057802.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, flush, 4 of a kind, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with deuces wild.

A057803.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, flush, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 2 jokers.

A057804.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, flush, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 1 joker.

A057805.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, flush, 4 of a kind, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with deuces wild.

A057806.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, flush, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 2 jokers.

A057807.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) 5 of a kind, a straight flush, 4 of a kind, flush, full house, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in wild-card poker with 1 joker.

A057808.name: Number of ways of getting (at least) a straight flush, 4 of a kind, full house, flush, straight, 3 of a kind, 2 pair, a pair in poker.

A057809.name: Numbers n such that pi(n) divides n.

A057810.name: Quotients n/pi(n) for n in A057809.

A057811.name: pi(n) is even.
formula: Chang & Li show that a(n) < 64n + o(1), and a(n) < 8n + o(1) under the Hardy-Littlewood prime tuples conjecture. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Dec 19 2014

A057812.name: pi(n) is odd.
formula: Chang & Li show that a(n) < 64n + o(1), and a(n) < 8n + o(1) under the Hardy-Littlewood prime tuples conjecture. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Dec 19 2014

A057813.name: a(n) = (2*n+1)*(4*n^2+4*n+3)/3.
formula: G.f. for sequence with interpolated zeros: 1/(8*x)*sinh(8*arctanh(x)) = 1/(16*x)*( ((1 + x)/(1 - x))^4 - ((1 - x)/(1 + x))^4 ) = 1 + 11*x^2 + 45*x^4 + 119*x^6 + .... Cf. A019560. - _Peter Bala_, Apr 07 2017

A057814.name: Number of partitions of an n-set into blocks of size > 4.
formula: a(0) = 1; a(n) = Sum_{k=5..n} binomial(n-1,k-1) * a(n-k). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Feb 09 2020

A057816.name: If a(n) = 0 mod 3 then a(n+1)=a(n)/3 otherwise a(n+1)=4*a(n)+-1 where sign is chosen to give a multiple of 3.

A057817.name: Moebius invariant of cographic hyperplane arrangement for complete graph K_n. Also value of Tutte dichromatic polynomial T_G(0,1) for G=K_n. Also alternating sum F_{n,1} - F_{n,2} + F_{n,3} - ..., where F_{n,k} is the number of labeled forests on n nodes with k connected components.
formula: a(n) = n^(n-2) - Sum_{k=1..n-1} binomial(n-1,k-1) * k^(k-2) * a(n-k). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Feb 07 2020

A057818.name: Number of factorable (see A057765 for definition) subsets of a 2 X n uniform grid.

A057820.name: First differences of sequence of consecutive prime powers (A000961).

A057821.name: a(n) is the least nonnegative integer k such that 2^n - k is a safe prime.

A057822.name: Smaller of pair of twin primes whose average is lcm(1,...,m) for some m.

A057823.name: The number q = 0.193072033... is the value of q which gives the maximum of the Dedekind eta function eta(q) := q^(1/12) * product_{n>=1} (1-q^(2n)) for q between 0 and 1.

A057824.name: Primes p such that p+1 is LCM[1,...,m] for some (usually more than one) m.

A057825.name: Values of k for which A003418(k) - 1 is prime.

A057826.name: Greatest number with totient 2n (or zero when no such number exists).

A057827.name: a(0) = 1; a(n) = LCM(n, sum{k=0 to n-1}[a(k)]).

A057828.name: Number of perfect squares, k^2, where k^2 <= n and gcd(k,n) = 1.

A057835.name: Difference between pi(10^n) and the integer nearest to 10^n / log(10^n).
formula: a(n) ~ 10^n/(n log 10)^2. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Mar 22 2015

A057836.name: Integers with 2 or more consecutive anti-divisors.

A057837.name: Number of partitions of a set of n elements where the partitions are of size > 3.
formula: a(0) = 1; a(n) = Sum_{k=4..n} binomial(n-1,k-1) * a(n-k). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Feb 09 2020

A057841.name: a(n) = 2^A057838(n) corresponding to extremal cases of A055079.

A057846.name: Sort the digits of n into alphabetical order (the "Obsessive Filer's Sequence").

A057847.name: Primes p such that order of primeness A049076(p) is > 10.

A057848.name: Number of 1-connected claw-free cubic graphs with 2n nodes.

A057849.name: Primes p such that order of primeness A049076(p) is > 7.

A057850.name: Primes p such that order of primeness A049076(p) is > 8.

A057851.name: Primes p such that order of primeness A049076(p) is > 9.

A057852.name: Numbers n such that n | Sigma_2(n) + Sigma_1(n) + Sigma_0(n).

A057853.name: Number of letters in n (in Esperanto).

A057854.name: Non-Lucas numbers: the complement of A000032.
formula: a(n) = floor(1/2 - LambertW(-1, -log(phi)/phi^(n+1/2))/log(phi)) with phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2. - Nicolas Normand (nicolas.normand (at) polytech.univ-nantes.fr)

A057855.name: Greatest k such that (k-th prime) <= (n times n-th prime).

A057856.name: Least k such that (n+1)^k + n^k is a prime.

A057857.name: Number of residue classes modulo n-th primorial number which contain a prime.

A057858.name: Number of residue classes modulo n-th primorial number which contain only composite numbers.

A057859.name: Number of residue classes modulo n which contain a prime.

A057860.name: Number of residue classes modulo n which contain only composite numbers.

A057863.name: a(n) = Product_{k=1..n} (2k-1)!!.
formula: a(n) ~ A^(1/2) * 2^(n^2/2+n+5/24) * n^(n^2/2+n/2+1/24) / exp(3*n^2/4+n/2+1/24), where A = 1.2824271291... is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (see A074962). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 13 2014
a(n) = 2^(n*(n+1)/2-1/24) * A^(3/2) * Pi^(-n/2-1/4) * exp(-1/8) * G(n+3/2), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant, G is the Barnes G-function. - _Vladimir Reshetnikov_, Nov 06 2015
a(n) = sqrt(G(2*n+2)) / (2^(n^2/2) * G(n+1) * sqrt(Gamma(n+1))), where G is the Barnes G-function. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 08 2021

A057864.name: Number of simple traceable graphs on n nodes.

A057865.name: Number of simple Hamilton-connected graphs on n nodes.

A057867.name: Denominator of coefficient of Pi^n in Ramanujan-like series for Zeta[4n+3].

A057868.name: Denominator of "modified Bernoulli number" b(2n) = Bernoulli(2*n)/(2*n*n!).

A057869.name: Triangle of coefficients of x^2 in the Neumann polynomials.

A057870.name: Number of singular points on n-th order Chmutov surface.
formula: Appears to satisfy a 13-term linear recurrence. - _Ralf Stephan_, Mar 07 2004

A057871.name: Numbers k such that 3*13^k + 2 is prime.

A057872.name: A version of the Chebyshev function theta(n): a(n) = round(Sum_{primes p <= n } log(p)).
formula: a(n) ~ n, a statement equivalent to the Prime Number Theorem. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 23 2012

A057873.name: a(1) = 1; a(n+1) = sum of terms in continued fraction for sum{k=1 to n}[a(n+1-k)/a(k)].

A057874.name: Sets of three composites in bidirectional 'sum of prime factors' progression/retrogression.

A057875.name: Numbers of 2n-digit primes which are concatenations of n-digit primes (no leading zeros allowed).

A057876.name: Primes p with the following property: let d_1, d_2, ... be the distinct digits occurring in the decimal expansion of p. Then for each d_i, dropping all the digits d_i from p produces a prime number.  Leading 0's are not allowed.

A057877.name: a(n) = smallest n-digit prime in A057876.

A057878.name: Primes with 2 distinct digits that remain prime (no leading zeros allowed) after deleting all occurrences of its digits d.

A057879.name: Primes with 3 distinct digits that remain prime (no leading zeros allowed) after deleting all occurrences of its digits d.

A057880.name: Primes with 4 distinct digits that remain prime (no leading zeros allowed) after deleting all occurrences of its digits d.

A057881.name: Primes with 5 distinct digits that remain prime (no leading zeros allowed) after deleting all occurrences of its digits d.

A057882.name: Primes with 6 distinct digits that remain prime (no leading zeros allowed) after deleting all occurrences of its digits d.

A057883.name: Smallest possible prime with at least n (from 2 to 10) distinct digits that remains prime (leading zeros not allowed) when all occurrences of its digits d are deleted.

A057884.name: A square array based on tetrahedral numbers (A000292) with each term being the sum of 2 consecutive terms in the previous row.
formula: T(n, k)=T(n-1, k-1)+T(n, k-1) with T(0, k)=1, T(4, 1)=4, T(0, 2n)=T(4, n) and T(0, 2n+1)=0. Coefficient of x^n in expansion of (1+x)^k/(1-x^2)^4.

A057885.name: Numbers n such that digits of n and the prime factorization of n are distinct and nonrepeating.

A057886.name: Number of integer 4-tuples that give the lengths of the sides of a nondegenerate quadrilateral with perimeter n.
formula: Conjecture: a(1)=0 and, for n>1, a(n)=a(n-1)+d(n-1), where d(n)=floor(n/4)*floor((n-2)/4) if n is even and d(n)=floor((n+1)/4) if n is odd.

A057887.name: Number of 4-tuples of integers with GCD=1 and giving the lengths of sides of a nondegenerate quadrilateral with perimeter n.

A057888.name: In Japanese: 1-digit numbers in a-i-u-e-o order, then 2-digit numbers in a-i-u-e-o order, etc.

A057889.name: Bit-reverse of n, including as many leading as trailing zeros.

A057890.name: In base 2, either a palindrome or becomes a palindrome if trailing 0's are omitted.

A057891.name: In base 2, neither a palindrome nor becomes a palindrome if trailing 0's are omitted.

A057895.name: Nonnegative numbers which can be written as m^k-m [with m and k nonnegative and 0^0 taken as 1].

A057896.name: Nonnegative numbers that can be written as m^k - m (with m and k nonnegative) in more than one way.

More generally, it appears that a(base,n)=a(base-1,n)+3^(n-1) for base>=n; a(base,n)=a(base-1,n)+3^(n-1)-2 when base=n-1. - _R. H. Hardin_, Dec 26 2006

A057977.name: GCD of consecutive central binomial coefficients: a(n) = gcd(A001405(n+1), A001405(n)).
formula: Recurrence: a(0) = 1 and a(n) = a(n-1)*n^[n odd]*(4/(n+2))^[n even] for n > 0.
Asymptotic formula: Let [n even] = 1 if n is even, 0 otherwise. Let N := n+1+[n even]. Then a(n) ~ 2^N /((n+1)^[n even]*sqrt(Pi*(2*N+1))).
E.g.f.: U(0) where U(k)= 1 + x/(1 - x/(x + (k+1)*(k+2)//U(k+1))); (continued fraction, 3-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Oct 19 2012

A057979.name: a(n) = 1 for even n and (n-1)/2 for odd n.
formula: a(n) = (n+1)/4+(3-n)*(-1)^n/4. - _Paul Barry_, Mar 21 2003, corrected by _Hieronymus Fischer_, Sep 25 2007
G.f.: (x^3-x^2+1)/(1-x^2)^2= 1 + x^2*G(0)  where G(k) = 1 + x*(k+1)/(1 - x/(x + (k+1)/G(k+1) )) ; (continued fraction,3-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Nov 29 2012
a(n) = binomial(floor(n/2), n mod 2). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Oct 14 2013
a(n) = 1 - n mod 2 * (1 - floor(n/2)). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 11 2014
a(n) = floor(n/2)^(n mod 2). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Mar 16 2015
